abstract: High-tech robotic parking garages, common in Europe, Middle East and Asia, have been site of embarrassing malfunctions in United States, where technology is lagging.
lead_paragraph: Software and hardware mishaps, including some that have smashed or trapped cars, have occurred at robotic garages around the country, but dozens of them are proposed or underway.

headline.main: Road to Robotic Parking Is Littered With Faulty Projects
headline.print_headline: Road to Robotic Parking in the U.S. Is Littered With Faulty Projects
